projects.name: Predictive Health Monitoring System: Integrating Full-Stack and ML
projects.description: Developed Predictive Health Monitoring System (PHMS) integrating full-stack architecture and ML techniques. Enabled personalized patient monitoring and early disease detection. Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript; Backend: Flask, MySQL for seamless integration and user authentication. Delivered real-time results with critical event detection and predictive recommendations, improving patient outcomes.

projects.name: Optimizing Medical Diagnosis through Ensemble Models in Machine Learning
projects.description: Conducted a study on the applications of machine-learning algorithms in medical condition classification. Analyzed real-world datasets covering heart disease, Pima diabetes, chronic kidney disease, thoracic surgery, and breast cancer. Focused on enhancing healthcare predictions, particularly for conditions with a stagnant prognosis. Evaluated the performance of various machine-learning models, including SVM, ANN, Stacked SVM, Stacked SVM with ANN, Bagged ANN, and Stacked SVM with ANN.

projects.name: Encrypted Communication Tool
projects.description: Utilized HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to replicate Netflixs user interface, demonstrating proficiency in front-end web development. Designed an intuitive user interface leveraging Tkinter, ensuring a seamless and user-friendly experience. Contributed to enhancing data privacy and security by providing a tool for secure message transmission.

experiences.description: Collaborated with faculty on machine learning research projects, focusing on medical data analysis. Executed a project on a diabetes dataset, employing various machine learning algorithms including Artificial Neural Networks (ANN), Naive Bayes, and K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN). Analyzed results and contributed to research findings presented to faculty and peers.
